    <title type="text">Encyclopaedia Iranica Crowdsource Tagging Project</title>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<a href="http://www.iranicaonline.org/pages/tag-project">Encyclopaedia
      Iranica Crowdsource Tagging Project</a> <br /><blockquote
      class="tr_bq"><img alt="" height="242"
      src="http://www.iranicaonline.org/uploads/images/Campaign_images/TagProject.jpg" width="450"
      /></blockquote><blockquote class="tr_bq"><span style="font-size:
      x-small;">The <em>Encyclopaedia Iranica</em> website can be searched by tags,
      and we are therefore launching a Tag Project to improve its tag search
      function.</span><br /> <span style="font-size: x-small;"><em><img
      alt="" height="105"
      src="http://www.iranicaonline.org/uploads/images/Campaign_images/Search-Function.jpg"
      width="450" /></em></span><br /> <span style="font-size:
      x-small;">In order to increase the number of descriptive keywords or short phrases
      associated with each entry, we are calling on our readers to submit tags (for more on tags and
      tagging, see the WIKI entry on “<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tag_%28metadata%29"
      target="_blank">Tag</a>”) when reading <em>Encyclopaedia Iranica
      Online</em> entries.</span><br /> <span style="font-size: x-small;">In
      order to submit tags, you will find on the right hand column of each entry, a
      <strong>Tag</strong> section under the <strong>Comments</strong>
      section. Click the <strong>Tags</strong> link on the left, and you will see tags
      already associated with an entry; if you click the <strong>Add a Tag</strong> link
      on the right, you will get a pop-up window that will allow you to add multiple tags separated
      by a comma (,).</span><br /> <span style="font-size: x-small;"><img alt=""
      height="213"
      src="http://www.iranicaonline.org/uploads/images/Campaign_images/Tag_crowdsourcing-image.jpg"
      width="450" /></span><br /> <span style="font-size: x-small;">We are
      looking forward to receiving your tags. Since we are moderating this project, we will
      acknowledge all submissions from readers who also wish to enter their email
      address.</span><br /> <span style="font-size: x-small;">If you have
      questions, please write to us at (<a
      href="mailto:iranica2011@gmail.com">iranica2011@gmail.com</a>).&nbsp;</span><br
      /><span style="font-size: x-small;">&nbsp;</span><br /> <span
      style="font-size: x-small;">Please feel free to tag along and many thanks in advance for
      your time and assistance!</span></blockquote><div style="text-align:
      center;">See also the 2012 <a
      href="http://ancientworldonline.blogspot.com/2012/07/encyclopaedia-iranica-crowdsourcing.html">Encyclopaedia
      Iranica Crowdsourcing Project</a></div><div style="text-align:
      center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a
      href="http://ancientworldonline.blogspot.com/2010/04/open-access-reference-encyclopdia.html">Online
      Encyclopædia Iranica entry at AWOL</a>&nbsp; </div>]]></content>
